net.hudup.core

Class PluginChangedEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • net.hudup.core.PluginChangedEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PluginChangedEvent
extends java.util.EventObject
    PluginStorage manages many RegisterTable (s) and each RegisterTable stores algorithms having the same type. For example, a register table manages recommendation algorithms (recommenders) whereas another manages metrics for evaluating recommenders. PluginStorageManifest which is the graphic user interface (GUI) allows users to manage PluginStorage. Every time PluginStorage was changed, this event PluginChangedEvent is issued and dispatched to a listener PluginChangedListener. Later on, PluginChangedListener can do some tasks in its method PluginChangedListener.pluginChanged(PluginChangedEvent). Please pay attention that such PluginChangedListener must be registered with PluginStorageManifest before to receive PluginChangedEvent.

    10.0
